Node.Notes: Uncertain. Perhaps "profuse" from abundant. Many change word slightly to yield "false/deceitful."
Uncertain. Perhaps "the pleasantness of his friend is from [his] earnest counsel." Some think "the sweetness of one's friend is more than one's own counsel."
Ketiv is "strangers"; qere is "strange woman" (see also pr27:13), which may simply be parallel to stranger or may indicate an alluring/wayward woman.
Literally, "hide," which most see as somehow indicating "restrain/control."
Uncertain. Most interpret as to meet/encounter (thus grasp) oil with his right hand.
Uncertain. Most revocalize to call to get to encounter and thus to grasp for this verb.
Most change a vowel for the verb to a passive form to yield "iron is sharpened by iron."
Most change the vowel for this verb to a causative active, yielding "a man sharpens the face of his friend," which may be figurative for causing his friend to be increase in perception/wit/energy.
Seems to mean that water reflects the face that looks into it.
Seems to mean that the heart is a mirror, by which knowledge of a man is gained. Not clear whether one's own heart or the heart of another is being looked into.
Seems to assume a verb like "is tested," since the crucible and furnace determine the purity of silver and gold.
